sh-app-fmt - Shell Application Formatter

USAGE:
    sh-app-fmt <shell-file>

DESCRIPTION:
    Format shell application files according to standard structure:
    - Header (#!/bin/sh)
    - REQUIRED_ARGUMENTS
    - lib statements (sorted)
    - constant statements (sorted)
    - cfg statements (sorted)
    - init statements (sorted)
    - Remaining content

ARGUMENTS:
    shell-file
        Shell file to format (required)

EXAMPLES:
    sh-app-fmt script.sh
    sh-app-fmt ~/project/bin/tool
